Final Exam Questions
What fundamentally causes external fragmentation?
  > segments of many different sizes having to be allocated contiguously

3 advantages of multi-level page tables over 1-level page tables?
  i.    swap pages
  ii.   can delay allocating memory until needed
  iii.  the page table no longer needs to be contiguous

(T/F) Cache and TLB both cache a part of the physical memory. [True]

Instances of using an extra level of indirection?
  i.    multi-level page tables
  ii.   dynamic memory relocation... base/bound, segmentation, etc
  iii.
